message.name: TEST_DATA
message.description: This message will send a single byte of data for debugging.
message.field: Holds raw data for use in testing

message.name: XBEE_HEARTBEAT
message.description: This message will send a single byte that will count and check that xbee is alive.
message.field: TRUE or FALSE if acknowledgement required.
Holds raw data for use in testing

message.name: MAVLINK_ACK
message.field: ID of message being acknowledged.
Status code of message being acknowledged.

message.name: CMD_OTHER
message.field: TRUE or FALSE if acknowledgement required.
Return to station (0x1), reinitialize boat (0x2), start override (0x3)

message.name: STATUS_AND_ERROR
message.description: Status and error codes used for debugging.
message.field: TRUE or FALSE if acknowledgement required.
Boat is initializing (0x1), boat is rescuing (0x2), boat rescue success (0x3), boat is returning to station (0x4), boat in override (0x5).
Error codes defined in Error.h

message.name: GPS_GEO
message.description: GPS geodetic coordinate used upon boat initialization for origin.
message.field: TRUE or FALSE if acknowledgement required.
Geodetic latitude position in degrees
Geodetic longitude position in degrees

message.name: GPS_ECEF
message.description: GPS geocentric, earth-centered, earth-fixed coordinate used for initialization or error correction.
message.field: TRUE or FALSE if acknowledgement required.
Command center's origin (0x1), or GPS error (0x2)
Geocentric x position in meters
Geocentric y position in meters
Geocentric z position in meters

message.name: GPS_NED
message.description: GPS command with NED local coordinate relative to command center used for initialization and to start a rescue.
message.field: TRUE or FALSE if acknowledgement required.
Set boat's station location (0x1), start a rescue (0x2), or report boat's location (0x3)
North component in meters.
East component in meters.
Down component in meters.

message.name: BAROMETER
message.description: Barometer data from boat containing temperature and altitude information.
message.field: TRUE or FALSE if acknowledgement required.
Contains the temperature in degrees Celsius.
Contains the altitude calculated from the barometer
